&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;📝&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a Product Owner to join the US Product team within Form3.&amp;nbsp;This role will act as a product expert for both internal teams and external stakeholders, driving continuous improvement and providing clarity on Form3’s full US Payments product suite.&amp;nbsp;With previous experience working across US A2A Payment rails, you will be supporting the wider team to make informed decisions, making a meaningful impact on the build and delivery of Form3’s US Payments products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate effectively across the FedNow, RTP, Fedwire, Zelle and ACH product lines, working closely with Product Owners and Product Managers to support the end-to-end delivery of payments solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the wider business to initiate and support the build of future products, such as Form3’s Zelle, Fedwire and ACH gateways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional Engineering teams across the US to translate product vision into actionable requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become a Subject Matter Expert on Form3’s full US payments product suite, offering guidance and clarity to both internal teams and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse the impact of product changes and enhancements quickly and effectively, shaping and documenting requirements to support continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take full ownership of certain tasks within the team, such as writing user stories, defining acceptance criteria, creating functional features and non-functional specifications, and analysing data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a high-level understanding of the overall US product line and underlying platform architecture to further inform decision-making and prioritisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WE ARE LOOKING FOR&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;🔍&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Form3’s Product team is a central function to the success of our US offering, we&#39;re therefore looking for an ambitious and versatile Product Owner who can act autonomously, whilst also working well as a key player within a close-knit and delivery focused team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Over 3 years experience in a Product Owner (Business Analyst) role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced working on US Payment gateway products (e.g. FedNow; RTP; ACH; Fedwire; Zelle), with in-depth knowledge of how these schemes work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability in writing user stories, defining acceptance criteria, and creating functional features and non-functional specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical experience working with API and/or cloud-based product offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with data analysis and presenting insights to a wide range of internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the full product development lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively across multiple internal teams, particularly within Engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate effectively in a fast-paced, high-growth environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience working on Zelle products, with demonstrated understanding of how Zelle differs to other US payment schemes and experience of implementing Zelle gateways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience within an external-facing role, in which partnering with customers / clients has been a core responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT FORM3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;💭

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;THE PROJECT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;📝&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;PDq2pG_selectionAnchorContainer&quot; data-start=&quot;230&quot; data-end=&quot;638&quot;&gt;As a Senior Software Engineer, you will be engaged to deliver key initiatives that strengthen the security and resilience of Form3&#39;s cloud-native payments platform. Working within a collaborative engineering environment, you will design, build, and implement capabilities that enhance the security, trust, and resilience of our systems while supporting the delivery of defined project outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;643&quot; data-end=&quot;1195&quot;&gt;This engagement is centred on hands-on software engineering and security-focused platform development. You&#39;ll apply your expertise across areas such as API security, cryptographic controls, AI governance, software supply chain security, and automated security tooling to deliver production-ready solutions. Working alongside engineers, platform specialists, and security experts, you&#39;ll focus on delivering scalable, maintainable capabilities that can be embedded into the software development lifecycle and provide lasting value beyond the engagement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
